node.text:
https://smittenkitchen.com/2007/10/butternut-squash-and-caramelized-onion-galette/

Did you miss my IG Live demo of making smittenkitchen.com's butternut squash and caramelized onion galette on Friday, 11/8? Good news! We finally figured out how to share and save it forever on IGTV (thank you to everyone who DMed me with tips). Hope you make it, too! [Butternut Squash and Caramelized Onion Galette on smittenkitchen.com]

node.text: A forever summer favorite, you do not need one fancy thing to make this, save the freshest clams you can find. You can pick them up on the way home from wherever you’ve been today, knowing that cooking dinner will be the easiest part of it. // Linguine and Clams on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. node.text: One of our favorite summer cakes, ever -- with sunken berries that melt into jammy puddles and edges that brown and become faintly crisp -- one-bowl-ed and ready to feed the crowd that forms whenever you make it. // Strawberry Summer Sheet Cake on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. node.text: Don't let tomato season pass without making these, doubly so if you've only had terrible ones to date. The rice absorbs the most clear-noted pure tomato sauce you’ll ever scoop onto a fork; the ingredient list couldn't be less complicated. It's total summer dinner bliss. // Rice-Stuffed Tomatoes on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile. node.text: My family's signature coffee cake is tall, plush, crisp with cinnamon sugar, and studded with a quilt of chocolate chips, and I know we are all about the 🍅🌽🫑🫐🍆 right now but do know that this is a forever favorite for those Jewish holidays that will be spectacularly early this year. It's also, just saying, good for Thursday nights. // Chocolate Chip Sour Cream Coffee Cake on smittenkitchen.com or linked in profile. In more detail: Go to my profile.
